LikeOS-64
=========

A modern 64-bit operating system built from scratch, featuring a Unix-like
userland with process management, syscalls, multitasking, SMP support, and
an interactive shell.

Current state
-------------

- Real hardware support: tested on Lenovo notebook with USB boot.
- Linux bootstrapper support: boot from Linux USB host and launch LikeOS in
  embedded QEMU.
- QEMU support: run with USB image targets.
- VMware support: USB 3.1 boot.
- VirtualBox support: xHCI (USB 3) and ICH9 chipset.
- UEFI boot is required.

Overview
--------

LikeOS-64 is a Unix-like operating system demonstrating modern OS development:

- Complete userland: ring 3 processes with syscall interface.
- Process management: preemptive multitasking scheduler.
- SMP support: BSP and AP startup with per-CPU scheduling data.
- UEFI bootloader: GNU-EFI based ELF64 kernel loading.
- Filesystems: FAT32 with VFS and devfs.
- Caching strategy: dentry cache, inode cache, and page cache.
- Hardware drivers: xHCI USB 3.0, USB mass storage, PS/2, PCI, APIC.
- Memory: physical/virtual memory, SLAB allocator, security protections.
- TTY and signals: POSIX-like terminal and signal handling.

Feature summary
---------------

Core OS
~~~~~~~
- 64-bit long mode kernel and higher-half mapping.
- UEFI boot path with framebuffer and memory map handoff.
- Interrupt and exception handling with IDT and PIC/APIC integration.

SMP (Symmetric Multi-Processing)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
- Up to 64 CPUs.
- AP startup using INIT-SIPI-SIPI and AP trampoline.
- Per-CPU data structures via GS base.
- Per-CPU run queues and scheduler accounting.
- LAPIC timer setup and SMP IPI support.
- IOAPIC routing for multi-core delivery.
- TLB shootdown helpers and SMP-aware locking paths.

Caching strategy
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
- Dentry cache:
  - Name lookup cache for directory entries.
  - Positive and negative dentry entries.
  - Hash buckets with LRU eviction.
- Inode cache:
  - Metadata cache keyed by inode number.
  - Reference counting and dirty metadata writeback.
  - Cached cluster chain acceleration for FAT32.
- Page cache:
  - File data pages (4 KiB) with hash-indexed lookup.
  - Read-ahead and sequential access optimization.
  - CLOCK-style eviction and dirty writeback handling.

Process management and userland
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
- fork, execve, exit, wait4, signals, pipes.
- User mode execution in ring 3.
- ELF64 user binary loading.
- Userland libc and dynamic runtime linker support.

User core utilities
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Included commands (selection):

- Shell and core navigation: sh, ls, pwd, cd behavior in shell.
- File tools: cat, cp, mv, rm, mkdir, rmdir, touch, stat, file, find.
- Text tools: grep, wc, sort, uniq, cut, tr, head, tail, strings, hexdump, nano.
- System tools: uname, uptime, date, time, ps, top, df, du, free, dmesg.
- Process tools: kill, sleep.
- Environment tools: env, which, echo, printf.
- Power tools: shutdown, poweroff, reboot, halt.
- Other utilities: clear, man, yes, true, false.
- Test programs: test_syscalls, test_libc, testmem, teststress, progerr.

Build
-----

Prerequisites (Ubuntu/Debian):

  sudo apt update
  sudo apt install gcc nasm xorriso mtools dosfstools ovmf gnu-efi-dev \
                   debootstrap parted gdisk qemu-utils grub-efi-amd64-bin rsync

Or:

  make deps

Build all:

  make all

Main build outputs:

- build/bootloader.efi
- build/kernel.elf
- build/bin/* user programs
- build/LikeOS-64.iso
- build/LikeOS-64.img
- build/LikeOS-64-usb.img
- build/msdata.img

Run
---

QEMU:

  make clean
  make qemu-usb

Other useful targets:

  make clean
  make usb-write USB_DEVICE=/dev/sdX
  make qemu-realusb USB_DEVICE=/dev/sdb

Linux USB host mode:

  make clean
  make linux-usb
  make linux-usb-write USB_DEVICE=/dev/sdX

Project structure
-----------------

- boot/: UEFI bootloader and trampoline.
- kernel/: kernel subsystems (ke, hal, mm, fs, io).
- include/kernel/: public kernel headers.
- user/: user programs (core utilities and tests).
- userland/libc/: C library and runtime pieces.
- host/linux-usb/: Linux host USB builder.
- ports/: third-party ports.

Implementation status
---------------------

Completed:
- UEFI bootloader and ELF64 loading.
- Multitasking scheduler and userland process model.
- SMP bring-up and per-CPU kernel infrastructure.
- Syscall layer, signals, pipes, and TTY.
- FAT32, VFS, devfs, and caching layers.
- xHCI USB stack and USB mass storage.
- Framebuffer console optimizations.
- Userland libc and core utilities set.

Planned/future work:
- Networking stack.
- Additional writable filesystems.
- More drivers (AHCI/NVMe/networking).
- Expanded POSIX coverage.
- GUI and package management improvements.

Contributing
------------

Contributions are welcome for kernel subsystems, drivers, userland tools,
performance tuning, and documentation.

